                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/13121a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-11T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 11, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>386. We have received further information from a high authority of a foreign
                        government<note n="30" xml:id="d832fn30">See telegram from Generalissimo
                        Chiang Kai-shek, <ref target="#pg_1004">p. 1004</ref>.</note> to the effect
                    that, according to reliable and most confidential reports reaching his
                    Government, Germany, Italy and Japan several days ago entered into a secret
                    agreement where-under Germany and Italy recognized the special position in the
                    Far East which Japan claims for herself and in return Japan agreed to take
                    action against French Indochina and Thailand and later to attack the Soviet
                    Union. A further such report from the same source was to the effect that Japan’s
                    moves southward and northward as described above would be carried out
                        simultaneously.<note n="31" xml:id="d832fn31">See also memorandum by the
                        Acting Secretary of State, July 10, <ref target="#pg_300">p.
                        300</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
